Virgin to Make Formal Bid for Lloyds Branches in July, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-05-25T23:07:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/virgin-to-make-formal-bid-for-lloyds-branches-in-july-ft-says.html
Virgin Group Ltd. will make a formal
bid in July for the 600 branches  Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  is
selling, the Financial Times reported, citing an interview with
Virgin Chairman  Richard Branson . Branson met Chief Executive
Officer Antonio Horta-Osorio on May 24, the FT said.  Virgin is a “serious bidder,” and the sale, which would
provide the increased market competition sought by the
government, “can happen quickly and smoothly,” Branson said,
according to the FT.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 